cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with a problem related to independent sets in graphs, which is a topic in both graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem is also related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) as the authors present a fixed-parameter algorithm. The problem is specifically studied on planar graphs (cs.CG), and the authors mention that their algorithm can be applied to a wider class of graphs, which may fall under discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
